Boolean

100> 1 == 1.0.
true
101> 1 =:= 1.0.
false

102> 1 /= 1.0.
false
103> 1 =/= 1.0.
true

Erlang operator compares int with floats where as regular one compares number with number


Tuples

110> X = 10, Y = 4.
4
111> Points = {X,Y}.
{10,4}
112> {X,Y} = Points.
{10,4}
113> X.
10

Lists

143> hd([1,2,3]).
1
144> tl([1,2,3]).
[2,3]

146> List = [1,2,3].
[1,2,3]
147> NewList = [1|List].
[1,1,2,3]

length([1]).


